definition.value: High molecular weight, linear polymers, composed of nucleotides containing deoxyribose and linked by phosphodiester bonds; DNA contain the genetic information of organisms.
A 5-oxo-2-furylacetic acid having a carboxy group at the 2-position.
An amino disaccharide that consists of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having an N-acetyl-4,6-di-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosaminyl residue attached at position 4.
An amino disaccharide that consists of 3-sulfated N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having a 3-sulfated N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl residue attached at position 4.
A guanidinium ion resulting from the protonation of the guanidyl group of camostat. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the galactosyl moiety is attached by a beta-linkage at the anomeric position and in which the N-acyl moiety bears a hydroxy group alpha- to the carboxamide group

A member of the class of imidazopyrimidopyrimidines that is 5,6-dihydroimidazo[1,2-a]pyrimido[5,4-e]pyrimidine substituted by [4-(morpholin-4-yl)phenyl]amino, oxo and 2,6-dichlorophenyl groups at positions 2, 5 and 6, respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of Wee-1 kinase (Ki = <10 nM).
An organic heterotricyclic compound that is imidazole which is ortho fused to a pyrimidine ring which itself is ortho fused to a pyrimidine ring.
A dicarboxylic acid monoester(1-) that is the conjugate base of 6-O-malonyl-trans-rhaponticin, resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A rhaponticin in which the double bond adopts a cis-configuration.
